pt.uc.dei.mobilerobotsimulator.Entity

    • Uses of Entity in pt.uc.dei.mobilerobotsimulator

      Subclasses of Entity in pt.uc.dei.mobilerobotsimulator 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Agent
      Agent represents the robot.
      class  ClosestAgent
      ClosestAgent uses strategy of the closest object: the next object to be visited is the one in the visual field that is geographically closer to the agent.
      class  DifferenceAgent
      This agent uses strategy of the maximum difference to the objects stored in memory: this strategy allows the agent to select as the next point of view the object that is more different to the objects in memory.
      class  Object
      Class Object represents subclass of the abstract class Entity, This class represents objects in our environment, e.q.
      class  RandomAgent
      RandomAgent uses random strategy: the next object to be visited is chosen randomly from the list of objects in the visual field.
